de.tub.data.dao
Interface IStaypointDAO<E>

All Superinterfaces:
IDao
All Known Implementing Classes:
Neo4JStaypointDAO
public interface IStaypointDAO<E>
extends IDao

This interface provides methods to access Stay Points. The IStaypointDAO is part of the Data Access Object design pattern.

Author:
Sebastian Oelke

Method Detail

createStayPoint

E createStayPoint(int id,
                  double latitude,
                  double longitude,
                  long arrivalTime,
                  long leavingTime)
Creates and saves a Stay Point.

Parameters:
id - the identifier of this Stay Point.
latitude - the latitude of this Stay Point.
longitude - the longitude of this Stay Point.
arrivalTime - the arrival time of this Stay Point in milliseconds (e.g., Date.getTime()).
leavingTime - the leaving time of this Stay Point in milliseconds (e.g., Date.getTime()).
Returns:
the created node or null if the node could not be created.

deleteStayPoint

void deleteStayPoint(int id)
Deletes the Stay Point with the given id.

Parameters:
id - the identifier of the Stay Point to delete.

findStayPointById

E findStayPointById(int id)
Finds a Stay Point by means of its identifier.

Parameters:
id - the identifier of the Stay Point to find.
Returns:
the Stay Point with the given identifier or null if no Stay Point was found.
